description: A lightweight javascript date library for parsing, manipulating, and formatting dates.
releaseNotes:
New languages
                - Serbian-Cyrillic (sr-cyr)
                - Khmer Cambodia (km)
            Features
                - Better handling of timezone-d moments around DST
                - Add weeksInYear and isoWeeksInYear
                - Support ordinal parsing
                - Composer support
                - Put Date parsing in moment.createFromInputFallback so it can be properly deprecated and controlled in the future
                - Extract two-digit year parsing in moment.parseTwoDigitYear, so it can be overwritten
                - Set AMD global before module definition to better support non AMD module dependencies used in AMD environment
                - Remove global in Node.JS environment (was not working before, nobody complained, was scheduled for removal anyway)
                - Support quarter setting and parsing
